<title>SRI LANKA: Sri Lanka decides against increasing tea imports.</title>
<headline>Sri Lanka decides against increasing tea imports.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-04-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sri Lanka has decided against letting in higher imports of tea for blending, fearing it could hurt prices at the world's biggest auction centre, government officials said on Monday.</p>
<p>&quot;We will maintain the status quo...we're not expanding imports,&quot; a Plantation Industries Ministry official said.</p>
<p>Sections of the tea trade had asked the government to allow imports of main grade orthodox teas for a limited trial period with the long-term aim of making Colombo a blending centre like London and Rotterdam.</p>
</text>
